        <mxCell id="legend" value="&lt;b&gt;Key properties vs K2.5 Agent Swarm&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br&gt;• &lt;b&gt;Heterogeneous models&lt;/b&gt;: non-K2 agents allowed (Kimi-powered subset only for core logic)&lt;br&gt;• &lt;b&gt;Heterogeneous devices&lt;/b&gt;: laptop · mobile · cloud all addressable&lt;br&gt;• &lt;b&gt;Persistent per-agent memory&lt;/b&gt;: each brings its own skill / tool / memory context&lt;br&gt;• &lt;b&gt;Humans as teammates&lt;/b&gt;, not just operators — human and agent deliverables mix in one run&lt;br&gt;• &lt;b&gt;Adaptive routing + auto recovery&lt;/b&gt;: coordinator detects stall, reassigns or regenerates subtask&lt;br&gt;• &lt;b&gt;Dogfooded internally&lt;/b&gt;: Kimi&#39;s own marketing team uses Claw Groups end-to-end" style="rounded=1;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;fillColor=#f1f5f9;strokeColor=#475569;fontSize=11;align=left;verticalAlign=top;spacingLeft=8;spacingTop=6" vertex="1" parent="1">
